nd"},"cs":{"1506–1594":"1506–1594","–Male":"Zesnulý","1530–Female":"1530–Zesnulá","1532–1587":"1532–1587","1539–Male":"1539–Zesnulý","25 January 1539":"25. ledna 1539","1587":"1587","1532":"1532","1530":"1530","1594":"1594","17 November 1587":"17. listopadu 1587","1506":"1506","from 1532 to 1537":"od 1532 do 1537","1539":"1539","Lavenham, Suffolk, England":"Lavenham, Suffolk, Anglie"},"da":{"1506–1594":"1506–1594","–Male":"Afdød","1530–Female":"1530–Afdød","1532–1587":"1532–1587","1539–Male":"1539–Afdød","25 January 1539":"25. januar 1539","1587":"1587","1532":"1532","1530":"1530","1594":"1594","17 November 1587":"17. november 1587","1506":"1506","from 1532 to 1537":"fra 1532 til 1537","1539":"1539","Lavenham, Suffolk, England":"Lavenham, Suffolk, England"},"nl":{"1506–1594":"1506–1594","–Male":"Overleden","1530–Female":"1530–Overleden","1532–1587":"1532–1587","1539–Male":"1539–Overleden","25 January 1539":"25 januari 1539","1587":"1587","1532":"1532","1530":"1530","1594":"1594","17 November 1587":"17 november 1587","1506":"1506","from 1532 to 1537":"van 1532 to 1537","1539":"1539","Lavenham, Suffolk, England":"Lavenham, Suffolk, England"},"en":{"1506–1594":"1506–1594","–Male":"Deceased","1530–Female":"1530–Deceased","1532–1587":"1532–1587","1539–Male":"1539–Deceased","25 January 1539":"25 January 1539","1587":"1587","1532":"1532","1530":"1530","1594":"1594","17 November 1587":"17 November 1587","1506":"1506","from 1532 to 1537":"from 1532 to 1537","1539":"1539","Lavenham, Suffolk, England":"Lavenham, Suffolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Payne","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from the Middle English and Old French personal name <i>Pai(e)n</i>, <i>Pagen</i> (from Latin <i>Paganus</i>), a fairly common personal name among Normans. It derived from a word that originally meant ‘villager, rustic’, later ‘heathen’, but it had doubtless lost these connotations in its use as a late medieval personal name. This name has also been established in Ireland since the 14th century.","History: Thomas Payne, who was a freeman of Plymouth Colony in 1639, was the founder of a large American family, which included Robert Treat Paine (1731–1814), one of the signers of the Declaration of Independence. See also   Paine  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Payn","meanings":["English (Kent): variant of   Payne  ."]},{"name":"Payen","meanings":["French: from the Old French personal name <i>Pagen</i>, <i>Paien</i>, from Latin <i>Paganus</i>, from <i>paganus</i> ‘country-dweller’, a derivative of <i>pagus</i> ‘of or relating to the countryside’, possibly given to a child not yet baptized (because of its later sense of ‘pagan, heathen’). Alternatively, a nickname for a country-born person. This surname is also found in the West Indies (mainly Haiti) and Mauritius.","English: variant of   Payne  ."]},{"name":"Pagan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Luis, Juan, Angel, Carlos, Rafael, Ramon, Pedro, Francisco, Jesus, Miguel, Julio.","Spanish and Catalan: Castilianized form (<b>Pagán</b>) of Catalan <b>Pagà</b>, from the Late Latin personal name <i>Paganus</i>, which as a derivative of Latin <i>pagus</i> ‘outlying village’ originally meant ‘villager’ (see   Payne  ). Alternatively, in some cases, a topographic name from Catalan <i>pagà</i> ‘heath’ (from the same Latin word <i>pagus</i>).","English: from the Middle English and Old French personal name <i>Pai(e)n</i>, <i>Pagen</i>, from Late Latin <i>Paganus</i> (see   Payne  , compare 1 above)."]},{"name":"Paynes","meanings":["English: variant of   Payne  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Paine","meanings":["English: variant of   Payne  .","History: The author of the republican treatise <i>The Rights of Man</i>, Thomas Paine (1737–1809), left England for North America in the mid 1770s, where he became involved in the movement that led to independence. His pamphlet of 1776, <i>Common Sense</i>, influenced the Declaration of Independence and furnished some of the arguments justifying it."]},{"name":"Pank","meanings":["English (Norfolk): perhaps from an unrecorded Middle English personal name <i>Pank(e)</i>. It could be a shortened form of <i>Pancok</i>, which is probably a pet form of <i>Pane</i> (see   Payne  ).","Sorbian: nickname from a diminutive of <i>pan</i> ‘mister, lord, landlord’ (see   Pan  ). Compare   Panke  ."]},{"name":"Pane","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Antonio, Salvatore, Aldo, Carmela, Carmine, Ciro, Concetta, Enzo, Giuseppe, Mario, Armando, Claudio, Macario, Remigio.","Italian: from <i>pane</i> ‘bread’, used as a metonymic occupational name for a baker or as a nickname meaning ‘good thing’, and also as a personal name. This surname is also found in southern France and Corsica.","English: variant of   Payne  ."]},{"name":"Panes","meanings":["English (Somerset): variant of   Payne  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Pannell","meanings":["English (southeastern):","possibly from Middle English <i>panel</i>, <i>panel(l)e</i> ‘cloth, saddle-cloth, saddle’ or ‘pane (of glass)’, hence a metonymic occupational name for a maker of such items.","from the Middle English personal name <i>Paynel</i> (Old French <i>Payenel</i>, Latin <i>Paganellus</i>), a pet form of   Payne   (from Latin <i>Paganus</i>)."]},{"name":"Penson","meanings":["English:","patronymic from the Middle English female personal name <i>Penn</i>, a pet form of <i>Pernel</i>, or perhaps from the Middle English personal name   Payne   + <i>-son</i>. See   Penn  ,   Parnell  .","habitational name from Penson in North Huish (Devon), which derives from the Anglo-Norman French personal name <i>Payn(e)</i> (see   Payne  ) + Middle English <i>toun</i> ‘village, town, settlement’ (Old English <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’)."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Payne was born in 1506, in Lavenham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with William Payne Sr. She died in 1594, at the age of 88."},"et":{"1506–1594":"1506–1594","–Male":"Surnud","1530–Female":"1530–Surnud","1532–1587":"1532–1587","1539–Male":"1539–Surnud","25 January 1539":"25. jaanuar 1539","1587":"1587","1532":"1532","1530":"1530","1594":"1594","17 November 1587":"17. november 1587","1506":"1506","from 1532 to 1537":"1532 kuni 1537","1539":"1539","Lavenham, Suffolk, England":"Lavenham, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1506–1594":"1506–1594","–Male":"Kuollut","1530–Female":"1530–Kuollut","1532–1587":"1532–1587","1539–Male":"1539–Kuollut","25 January 1539":"25. tammikuuta 1539","1587":"1587","1532":"1532","1530":"1530","1594":"1594","17 November 1587":"17. marraskuuta 1587","1506":"1506","from 1532 to 1537":"vuodesta 1532 vuoteen 1537","1539":"1539","Lavenham, Suffolk, England":"Lavenham, Suffolk, England"},"fr":{"1506–1594":"1506–1594","–Male":"Décédé","1530–Female":"1530–Décédée","1532–1587":"1532–1587","1539–Male":"1539–Décédé","25 January 1539":"25 janvier 1539","1587":"1587","1532":"1532","1530":"1530","1594":"1594","17 November 1587":"17 novembre 1587","1506":"1506","from 1532 to 1537":"du 1532 au 1537","1539":"1539","Lavenham, Suffolk, England":"Lavenham, Suffolk, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mrs Payne est née en 1506, à Lavenham, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 2 fils et 1 fille avec William Payne Sr. Elle est décédée en 1594, à l’âge de 88 ans."},"de":{"1506–1594":"1506–1594","–Male":"Verstorben","1530–Female":"1530–Verstorben","1532–1587":"1532–1587","1539–Male":"1539–Verstorben","25 January 1539":"25. Januar 1539","1587":"1587","1532":"1532","1530":"1530","1594":"1594","17 November 1587":"17. November 1587","1506":"1506","from 1532 to 1537":"von 1532 bis 1537","1539":"1539","Lavenham, Suffolk, England":"Lavenham, Suffolk, England","lifeSummary":"Mrs Payne wurde 1506 in Lavenham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatte mit William Payne Sr mindestens 2 